                "txt": "Our family enjoyed a fantastic stay at Beach Escape to celebrate my mum's 60th birthday. \nThere was a lot of planning and logistics in the lead up to our stay and Bailey was always prompt and accommodating with questions. \nIt's a great house for a large family, offering us the perfect bedroom configuration for 9 adults and 4 kids as well as plenty of living space so we weren't living on top of each other. \nWe loved the beautiful Pittwater views and dining outdoors on the large deck facing the view.\nBeach Escape is also pet friendly which meant all our family were welcome. \nIt was fantastic having the amenities of Avalon only 5 mins drive away but feeling like we were in a quiet secluded area far away from the hustle & bustle of Sydney. \nThere's plenty of pedestal fans but no air con & blinds on west facing windows made for a hot stay on the days that reached almost 40 degrees. But it meant we made the most of the wonderful harbour beach down the stairs. \nWould highly recommend Beach Escape to large groups. "
